title: Royal Family rocked by ‘biggest scandal since abdication’ after Andrew’s arrest
description: Sky News contributor Sophie Elsworth weighs in on the arrest of disgraced Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor, describing it as one of the “biggest scandals” to hit the Royal Family.  “Those pictures have now been beamed around the world of Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor … sitting in the back seat of a four-wheel drive, it looks like, looking quite startled,” Ms Elsworth told Sky News Australia.   “This is just extraordinary that we have one of the most senior members of the Royal Family all day in police questioning.   “This has absolutely shocked the British public; it’s shocked the monarchy.  “The world is just coming to terms with what some here in Britain have deemed the biggest scandal to hit the Royal Family since the abdication in 1936.”

title: Trump to ‘force’ deal from ‘vulnerable’ Iran with US military power
description: Democrat strategist Jim Kessler claims US President Donald Trump will use US military power to force a nuclear deal from Iran.  “Trump’s desire is to cut a deal,” Mr Kessler told Sky News Australia.  “He will use military power, not American boots on the ground, but air power to try and force that deal.”

title: ‘Only the beginning’ for Andrew following the former prince’s shocking arrest
description: Sky News contributor Sophie Elsworth says Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor’s arrest over alleged potential misconduct in public office raises further questions about whether additional action will follow regarding the sexual misconduct claims.  “There are questions being raised, perhaps this is only the beginning of the policing because we know he … was arrested today in relation to suspicion of alleged misconduct in public office,” Ms Elsworth told Sky News Australia.   “But now, many questions are being asked if there will be further action taken in relation to allegations of sexual misconduct.”

title: ‘The world is waiting’: Pressure builds on Charles to publicly address Andrew’s arrest
description: Sky News contributor Sophie Elsworth claims the world is waiting to see if King Charles publicly addresses disgraced former prince Andrew’s arrest.   “Today is the former prince’s 66th birthday; there were certainly no celebrations for him today,” Ms Elsworth told Sky News Australia.   “He probably hadn’t even eaten his breakfast, and police are knocking on his front door.   “This is a massive scandal that is gripping the British monarchy, and now the world is waiting to see whether the King will address the public.”

title: ISIS brides require security check sequence to ‘slow down’ return
description: Former Home Affairs secretary Mike Pezzullo discusses alternative sequences for the ISIS brides' return.  “Whether you like it or not, they’ve got a right of return,” Mr Pezzullo told Sky News Australia.  “There are a number of steps that you can put in place which are not about facilitating their return, it’s about actually checking their return and slowing it down.”

title: 'Nobody is above the law': Starmer sends a chilling warning on former prince Andrew
description: UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer says anyone with relevant information in the Epstein case, including Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor, should testify – just hours before the former prince was arrested.  Speaking to the BBC on Thursday and before news emerged of Andrew’s arrest, Starmer said decisions rest with investigators but stressed that “everybody is equal under the law and nobody is above the law".  He said that the principle must apply in this case as it would in any other, as scrutiny around Andrew intensifies.  It comes as Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor has been released from police custody in Norfolk after his arrest on suspicion of misconduct in public office.  The former prince was arrested at his home on Sandringham Estate in Norfolk on his 66th birthday.  Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor has always denied any wrongdoing regarding his relationship with Jeffrey Epstein.

title: ‘From Royal Lodge to a police cell’: Andrew’s dramatic fall from grace
description: Sky News contributor Sophie Elsworth discusses disgraced Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor’s “fall from grace” following his arrest over alleged potential misconduct while in public office.  “This scandal has been engulfing the Royal Family for some time; it was only in October that he [King Charles] stripped him of his royal titles and told him to pack his suitcases and get out of Royal Lodge,” Ms Elsworth told Sky News Australia.  “He has gone from a 30-room Royal Lodge mansion at Windsor estate to a police station in Norfolk.  “Presumably, you know, he was held in a cell for some period; he can’t be treated any differently than a member of the public.”

title: Stephen A Smith brutally calls out Gavin Newsom for dodging interview over California’s issues
description: Sports commentator Stephen A Smith has ruthlessly called out California Governor Gavin Newsom for dodging an interview.  During a Wednesday episode of his 'Straight Shooter' podcast, Smith claimed he was "still waiting" to chat with Newson to "answer" for California's issues.  Smith listed several problems facing the Golden State, such as homelessness, crime and California's sanctuary city status.  "Gavin Newsom, 22%. Still waiting for you to come on the show, Mr Governor. I keep telling you, it's going to be more, far more pleasant than you realise. Because I just want to ask questions and I want to listen to your answers," Smith said.  "I don't want a 'got you' moment. I don't want to make you uncomfortable. I don't want to go back and forth with you, interrogating you like I'm some prosecutor or whatever."

title: Trump blasts Obama for exposing ‘classified’ secrets about the existence of aliens
description: Barack Obama’s claims about aliens being real just got more interesting after US President Donald Trump came out and blasted the former president for releasing classified information.

title: ‘Haven't answered basic questions’: Angus Taylor blasts Labor over ISIS bride crisis
description: Opposition Leader Angus Taylor claims the Labor government has not answered basic questions on the ISIS bride crisis.  “The government has not answered the most basic questions,” Mr Taylor said.  “We just don’t have answers, and this is what we always see with this Labor government.”

title: Trump starkly warns something ‘unfortunate’ will happen to Iran if a nuclear deal is not made
description: US President Donald Trump has warned Iran to come to the negotiation table to make a nuclear deal.  The president's comments came while taking questions on Air Force One following the Board of Peace meeting.  Trump said if no deal was reached, something "unfortunate" would happen to Iran.  The president goes on to say Iran has 10 to 15 days "maximum to make" the deal. Trump also made remarks on Iran during his Board of Peace address.  The president's comments come amid the US buildup of military assets in the Middle East to pressure Iran.  Republican Strategist John Jordan claims a US strike on Iran is "nearly inevitable" as US military assets stand ready in the Middle East.

title: Trump crushes AOC and Newsom for ‘horrible’ performance in Munich
description: US President Donald Trump has savagely ridiculed Democrats Gavin Newsom and Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez (AOC) for their performance during the Munich Security Conference.  The president's harsh criticisms came during his Board of Peace address in Washington, DC.  Trump started by calling out Gavin Newsom, claiming he "didn't know why he was there".  The president then moved on to AOC's multiple gaffes, saying she may have given a "career-ending" answer.  Even Vice President JD Vance had a swipe at AOC when he made remarks blasting her for "freezing" in Munich.

title: Awkward laughter as Trump jokes about firing Rubio for epic Munich speech
description: US President Donald Trump jokingly threatened to fire Secretary of State Marco Rubio after his successful speech at the Munich Security Conference during a Board of Peace meeting in Washington DC.  Speaking at the first meeting of his Board of Peace at the United States Institute of Peace, Trump teased Rubio for doing “so well” in Munich that some asked why Trump doesn’t speak the same way.  “But Marco, don’t do any better than you did — because if you do, you’re out of here,” Trump quipped, drawing laughs from the room.

title: Epstein-linked Andrew remains under investigation following humiliating arrest
description: Disgraced ex-Prince Andrew will remain under investigation following his arrest on suspicion of misconduct in public office.  On Thursday, Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor was arrested on his 66th birthday, marking the first time in modern history a Royal Family member was taken into custody.  The disgraced prince was arrested under suspicion that he shared sensitive information with paedophile Jeffrey Epstein when serving as a UK trade envoy.  Following his arrest, UK police were seen searching Andrew’s Windsor Estate and the Wood Farm property, where he served as an envoy from 2001 to 2011.  The ex-prince has strongly denied any wrongdoing in connection with sex trafficker and paedophile, Epstein.
